commit.message:
Fix array of cookies in response containing a blank cookie

Without the fix, the blank cookie is compared and since it has no name
the comparison fails on name.downcase. Rather than correct it there, this
expands the processing of merged cookies to remove blank cookies not just
in strings, but also in arrays.
Add Ruby 3.3 to CI and bump actions/checkout to v4

Remove use of finalizer in Rack::Test::UploadedFile (Fixes #338)

A finalizer was used in the Tempfile case to close and unlink the
Tempfile created, but it was never needed, because Tempfile defines
its own finalizer that closes and unlinks.

Update the spec so that it actually tests that tempfiles are getting
removed and unlinked. This uses 500 tempfiles in the JRuby test
because some lower values I tried failed CI.  CRuby could likely get
away with only a handle of tempfiles, but the spec uses 50 to be
sure it doesn't fail.

Prefer Dir.glob with block

Dir#[] uses rb_push_glob in its implementation.
Stop testing Ruby 2.2 in CI as it no longer works with ubuntu-latest
Move to actions/checkout@v3
Add README.md to doc
Release 2.1.0
Update History.md

Don't raise error with empty params and multipart header

POST request with empty params and multipart header raises a `Rack::EmptyContentError` since 5b4bbfff166fc7c92ea9f33dc181c393ebeee96c.
https://github.com/rack/rack/blob/v3.0.4.1/lib/rack/multipart/parser.rb#L415-L419
Update CHANGELOG

Fix tests when rack master branch is used

Fix a spec description while here.

Ignore leading dot when merging cookies

Most recent specification states that leading dots are ignored by user
agents: https://httpwg.org/specs/rfc6265.html#sane-domain

commit.message: Bump cgi version in Ruby 3.1 CI test
Add CI for Ruby 3.2
Test JRuby 9.4 in CI
change order of arguments for `assert_equal` example in README
Make the UploadedFile GC finalizer test more reliable on CRuby

Avoid unnecessary Regexp match

Switch to using String#start_with?.  While here, inline the path
comparison into matches? instead of having a separate valid_path?
only called by matches?.
match path in #matches? rather than introduce new methods
cookie paths not applicable when setting

Don't add lib to the load path when running specs

This isn't needed, and it's helpful to ensure that the internals
are using require_relative instead of require.

Support default_host in Rack::Test::Methods

This allows you to configure a default host the same way you
configure the application.

Fixes #317

Add Session#restore_state for restoring previous state after block execution

This type of API is very helpful for testing access control in
applications.  I currently do something similar in the
capybara-restore_state gem, but that reaches into rack-test
internals, and I would like to have a public API for this so it
isn't necessary to do so.
